<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="457" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="74.[163,1070,914,1053]" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">
R e c o g n i t i o n The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[541,703,914,935]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Ammophila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="74" pageNumber="457" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meridionalis">
<emphasis box="[541,703,914,935]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">A. meridionalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a gastral apex black without metallic shine, the supra-antennal lamellate projection absent and the episternal sulcus probably extending to the anteroventral margin of the pleuron (covered with appressed setae on the 
<typeStatus box="[292,340,1002,1023]" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">type</typeStatus>
). Additionally, the mesothoracic venter is not prominent anteriorly, the arolia are well developed and the claws without basal tooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="74.[163,1071,1068,1412]" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">
D e s c r i p t i o n 3: Black, with following red: mandible (except apex), fore- and midlegs, hindleg (partly black), tergum I (except black dorsal strip), tergum II (except small black spot basally), tergum III and sterna II-IV; in some specimens petiole partly red. Head (except vertex), thorax and propodeum laterally covered with dense, appressed, silvery setae that obscure underlying sculpture and long erect white setae; legs partly covered with fine, appressed setae. Clypeus elongate (
<figureCitation box="[788,878,1215,1237]" captionStart="Figs 216-226" captionStartId="148.[163,203,1455,1475]" captionTargetBox="[171,1041,209,1430]" captionTargetId="figure-1@148.[163,1070,204,1434]" captionTargetPageId="148" captionText="Figs 216-226: male clypeus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341177/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">Fig. 222</figureCitation>
), dorsal surface of pronotal collar sparsely punctate. Scutum punctate (punctures one diameter apart), scutellum and metanotum punctate. Propodeal enclosure along midline coarsely rugose, covered with appressed silvery setae and also with white erect setae, laterally transversely ridged and glabrous. Mesopleuron, metapleuron and propodeum densely punctate. Collare laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[445,534,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figs 262-276" captionStartId="152.[163,203,1453,1473]" captionTargetBox="[172,1062,223,1433]" captionTargetId="figure-1@152.[163,1070,204,1433]" captionTargetPageId="152" captionText="Figs 262-276: pronotal collar of male in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341185" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341185/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">Fig. 265</figureCitation>
; gonostyle laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[752,842,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figs 374-389" captionStartId="159.[163,203,1499,1519]" captionTargetBox="[179,1065,225,1471]" captionTargetId="figure-1@159.[163,1070,204,1479]" captionTargetPageId="159" captionText="Figs 374-389: male genitalia: gonostyle in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341199/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">Fig. 379</figureCitation>
; penis valve laterally: 
<figureCitation box="[163,250,1390,1412]" captionStart="Figs 444-460" captionStartId="164.[163,203,1430,1450]" captionTargetBox="[178,1060,219,1396]" captionTargetId="figure-1@164.[163,1060,196,1409]" captionTargetPageId="164" captionText="Figs 444-460: male genitalia: penis valve in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341209" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341209/files/figure.png" pageId="74" pageNumber="457">Fig. 449</figureCitation>
. Flagellomere I: II= 2.0 (?); length of petiole = hindtarsomeres I+II+0.3×III.
</paragraph>
